http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Minister-satisfied-with-work/article13983756.ece

Health Minister V.S. Sivakumar has said that construction activities that are being undertaken beneath the Thakaraparambu flyover are progressing in a time-bound manner.Expressing satisfaction over the pace of the ongoing works, Mr. Sivakumar said that the 80-mm pipeline for the JICA-assisted drinking water supply project had been laid. The process of testing pressure of water supply would be undertaken within two days, he said, after conducting a site visit on Tuesday.He was assured by the official concerned that the stretch would be handed over for road development within January 9, according to an official release.